1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:23,000
 [Music]

2
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
 What's going on, Porch?

3
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
 How we doing, Fort Worth? We got people listening all over the world.

4
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 We're so glad that you're tuning in. Let me say this up front.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:42,000
 These churches just around the country are gathering in rooms and putting on the porch.

6
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
 And I'm so proud of you that you have caught a vision of what God wants to do through young adults,

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
 20s and 30-somethings, to change the world, to reclaim the world for the sake of Christ.

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 I want you to know that I prayed for you today, I thought about you, and I'm crazy encouraged that you would gather in this way

9
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,000
 and just kind of join this movement that God is doing in spite of us.

10
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 And so we are back in 1 Peter 2, focusing on two primary verses this evening.

11
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,000
 I'll read them to you.

12
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:25,000
 "Dear friends," verse 11, "Dear friends, I urge you as foreigners and exiles to abstain from sinful desires which wage war against your soul.

13
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
 Live such good lives among the pagans that, though they accuse you of doing wrong,

14
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:37,000
 they may see your good deeds and glorify God on the day He visits us."

15
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
 Let me pray.

16
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:45,000
 God, we love you, we thank you so much for your servant Peter, who walked with Jesus,

17
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:52,000
 who saw Jesus firsthand as an example, and who scribed these letters to the scattered church

18
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:59,000
 that you have preserved for thousands of years so that we might open tonight

19
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:04,000
 and that your Holy Spirit would minister to us through the reading and the preaching of your Word.

20
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:09,000
 Father, protect these friends from my opinion.

21
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:16,000
 And Father, awaken our hearts to your desires so that we may live them.

22
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
 In Jesus' name, amen. Amen.

23
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
 Anybody here like to travel?

24
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,000
 Okay.

25
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
 I love to travel.

26
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
 Monica and I love to travel, love to go new places.

27
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
 Didn't travel much growing up.

28
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,000
 Growing up, vacation was like San Antonio.

29
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
 We wanted to go real big.

30
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
 We'd go to the Guadalupe, like tube the river or something.

31
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
 That was doing it right.

32
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
 And so just didn't really see the world much growing up.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:52,000
 And then when I became a Christian as an adult in my 20s, it was interesting

34
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:56,000
 because instantly I started going on these discipleship trips.

35
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,000
 One of the first trips I went on was to Rwanda in Africa,

36
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
 and we were training the government on conflict resolution.

37
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:09,000
 And so when you go on a trip like that, you're thinking about what it's going to be like.

38
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
 You have no idea.

39
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:14,000
 You just don't know what it's going to be like when you get there.

40
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
 And so I had all of this anticipation, this long plane ride,

41
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:23,000
 and as soon as I get off the plane and leave the airport, I'm walking down the street,

42
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,000
 and these kids kind of gather around me.

43
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
 They're like, "Mzungu, Mzungu, Mzungu."

44
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
 They're like, "Tall white man."

45
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
 I guess that's what that means.

46
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
 And so you instantly realize you're not home.

47
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 They're like, "Foreigner, foreigner."

48
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:42,000
 And so then the next day I wake up to teach, and it's hot.

49
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:46,000
 It's like 108 degrees, and so I'm in shorts.

50
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 And they're like, "No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

51
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
 You can't wear shorts. Why? It's hot."

52
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:57,000
 I'm like, "Oh, no. Here, only boys under 10 years of age wear shorts.

53
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
 Like if you're over 10, you wear pants."

54
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,000
 And I'm like, "I'm trying to get my head around this,

55
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 but there's things that you want to know if you're a foreigner, right?

56
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
 You want to understand their culture."

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:11,000
 And so they're essentially saying, "No, you're about to teach in like a Spongebob Squarepants shirt or something."

58
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
 And if you wore one, I'm sorry. You shouldn't.

59
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,000
 And so they're like, "They're helping me. You can't do that."

60
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
 And so there are all these things I began to learn.

61
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:26,000
 Like we went to have a meal, and you know, in America, it's like women first, ladies go first.

62
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
 There, it's elderly first.

63
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:31,000
 And so whoever's the oldest, they would go first.

64
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:36,000
 And if you went to kind of grab food, you would never use your left hand

65
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:41,000
 because your left hand was your sanitizing hand.

66
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 Your left hand was the one you'd use to clean yourself after you went to the restroom.

67
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
 I didn't know either, right?

68
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
 And so if you're there in the lunch line, and you reach for the spoon with your left hand,

69
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,000
 everybody's like, "Oh, man, we're done."

70
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,000
 And I'm like, "Well, somebody should have told me.

71
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:01,000
 I didn't know that's what that hand was for."

72
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:09,000
 And what's interesting is when you would walk with someone, like a man, a brother in Christ,

73
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:14,000
 they'd grab your hand, and they'd walk with you hand in hand.

74
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:19,000
 They would interweave the fingers.

75
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
 It's not awkward. It's not awkward.

76
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,000
 Like that's what I kept telling myself.

77
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,000
 And so much so that when I was teaching through the translator, through the interpreter,

78
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
 that's the first thing that he did was he reached for my hand,

79
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
 and the whole time I'm preaching, we're walking around hand in hand, he and I,

80
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 fingers interlocked like we're on a date.

81
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:44,000
 And when you would greet someone, when you would greet someone,

82
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:49,000
 you would bump foreheads and then kiss each cheek.

83
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
 I didn't know, you know?

84
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:55,000
 And I'm a tall guy, and so the dude goes in for this like Muay Thai clinch and like pulls me down,

85
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
 and it's like this awkward kind of first kiss.

86
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
 I'm like, "What are we doing here?"

87
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:05,000
 And I just wish I knew, you know?

88
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,000
 I wish someone would have told me about this.

89
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
 And so this is true for when you go to different places.

90
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,000
 In Israel, I was on the Temple Mount with Monica,

91
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,000
 and I had my hand on her back like this,

92
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
 and we were stopped by the authorities.

93
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,000
 You can't even be in close proximity with someone of the opposite sex.

94
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 It is illegal to touch a woman in this area.

95
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
 I mean like hold hands or anything.

96
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:37,000
 We're about to get arrested because I'm walking with my wife with my hand on her back.

97
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
 Who knew? Like I wish I would have known this stuff.

98
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,000
 In Jordan, if you compliment someone on anything, like you say,

99
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,000
 "Man, I really like that picture," they'll give it to you

100
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
 just because the culture is so hospitable.

101
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
 If you say, "Man, what a beautiful place you have,"

102
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
 they're like, "Here's the keys. You want my house? What?"

103
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,000
 And like somebody needs to tell me these things.

104
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:02,000
 In the Amazon, if they cook something for you and they offer it to you,

105
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:08,000
 it is incredibly offensive not to eat it right there.

106
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:13,000
 Whatever it is, and you might not know, like one guy got boiled ants.

107
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
 And yeah, we didn't know what it was,

108
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:21,000
 but it's like you eat it or you have offended an entire people group.

109
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:28,000
 In Haiti, if you shake one person's hand, you have to shake everyone's hand.

110
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
 And so like we're in this church of like a thousand people,

111
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,000
 and I'm like, "Oh, hey, how you doing?"

112
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
 And then people are lining up. I'm like, "Oh, take that back."

113
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,000
 You know, what's up?

114
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,000
 And so it's just good to know these things if you're a foreigner.

115
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:46,000
 If you go somewhere, it is important to know the do's and the don'ts of that place.

116
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,000
 And so in these two verses of 1 Peter 2,

117
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:53,000
 Peter is going to remind us that we are like foreigners.

118
00:07:53,000 --> 00:08:00,000
 And he's going to give us the do's and don'ts of surviving this world as a follower of Christ.

119
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:06,000
 And the problem with this text is if you've come to faith as a 20-something or a 30-something,

120
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,000
 then what has happened is you've kind of started to understand the world.

121
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
 Like some of you, you're like, "Dude, I got the world.

122
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
 Like I'm great at the world. I know how to dress. I know the language to talk.

123
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:21,000
 I know how to make money. I can do good in business. I'm pretty. I'm cute. I'm handsome."

124
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,000
 Right? "I understand the world."

125
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:28,000
 And then you come in and you collide with Jesus, and it's like you're learning to walk all over again.

126
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,000
 And you're like, "Man, these Christians are goofy. Like how do I--I don't even know.

127
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:36,000
 Like how do I reprioritize everything? And can you even have fun as a Christian?"

128
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:41,000
 And you're learning a new world.

129
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:47,000
 And that's the world that Peter's going to talk to us about today.

130
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:51,000
 And I think a barrier to this message is that for so many of us,

131
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:56,000
 we think that Christianity is an idea that you add to your life.

132
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,000
 And friends, it's not.

133
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 It's the thrust of your life.

134
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
 It's the trajectory of your life.

135
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:07,000
 It's the road of your life and the vehicle traveling on that road.

136
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
 And it's what makes that vehicle go.

137
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 Christianity is everything. It is all-encompassing.

138
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,000
 It's who you are if you have a relationship with Jesus.

139
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,000
 It is not an accessory.

140
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,000
 You cannot view it as an accessory.

141
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,000
 It changes everything about you.

142
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:28,000
 As David said last week, it changes your purpose.

143
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,000
 And we're going to look at how to survive in this world.

144
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:35,000
 Like if you're here and you think about--when you dream about the future,

145
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:39,000
 you simply dream about maximizing your life in this world.

146
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
 You simply dream about the next 40 or 60 years.

147
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,000
 You don't get it.

148
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 That you're an eternal being.

149
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
 You're going to live somewhere forever.

150
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:51,000
 Your soul is going to exist somewhere for eternity.

151
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,000
 Forever and ever and ever.

152
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 600 years from now, still going.

153
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
 600 billion years from now, still going.

154
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,000
 You're still somewhere.

155
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,000
 That's the future. That's your future.

156
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 We have to get that we belong to that world, which is here.

157
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 So more on that. We are like a foreigner.

158
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,000
 So we're talking about how to live like a foreigner.

159
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,000
 We're in 1 Peter. Peter was a friend of Jesus.

160
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
 As I said, he knew him. He walked with him.

161
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:22,000
 He denied him. And then he was restored to him in John chapter 21.

162
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,000
 He was a fisherman turned fisher of men.

163
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:30,000
 He wrote this book to the Jews and the Greeks

164
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:34,000
 that have trusted in Christ who were scattered around Asia Minor,

165
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:39,000
 which is modern day Turkey, about 30 years after Jesus died.

166
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,000
 And so we're going to, as we move through these two verses,

167
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,000
 we're going to talk about how you're not home,

168
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 what you don't do, and what you must do as a foreigner.

169
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
 He says in verse 11,

170
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,000
 "Dear friends, I urge you as foreigners and exiles

171
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:58,000
 to abstain from sinful desires which wage war against your soul."

172
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,000
 We're going to hit on this idea of strangers and exiles.

173
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:04,000
 He's saying this, "Don't settle for this world."

174
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:08,000
 That's my first point. You cannot settle for this world.

175
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,000
 Don't settle in.

176
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:14,000
 "Live as" verse 11 says, "foreigners and exiles."

177
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,000
 And so the people that you are surrounded by in this world,

178
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,000
 they are not your people.

179
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,000
 They don't belong to the kingdom that you belong to.

180
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,000
 You don't want to get swept up in that culture.

181
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,000
 You're different. You're to stand apart from them.

182
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,000
 The apostle Paul tells us,

183
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:36,000
 "Like stars against a dark night that stand in contrast."

184
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:43,000
 That you're to shine as you live in this place that you don't belong to.

185
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,000
 And the place that you live in,

186
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,000
 now we're going to go theology, deep water a little bit.

187
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:53,000
 The place that you live in is not what it will be.

188
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:57,000
 Christ is going to come back here and it's going to be a new earth

189
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 that we're going to live in forever and ever and ever and ever.

190
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,000
 Heaven is here.

191
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:04,000
 Heaven's not this place that you float up to in the clouds with angels and harps.

192
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,000
 Heaven's going to be here.

193
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 And what this does, see, as I said, I like to travel.

194
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,000
 And there's this angst in me that I want to see the world.

195
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
 I want to go to places.

196
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,000
 Whenever I travel, I want to go somewhere that I've never been.

197
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,000
 And I want to experience it.

198
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,000
 And I want new experiences.

199
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,000
 And if I don't, and you go somewhere that I haven't been,

200
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,000
 I feel like I'm missing out.

201
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,000
 I'm looking on your Instagram feed and I'm like #fomo everywhere.

202
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:35,000
 I want to go and see it all.

203
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:42,000
 But the fact that I'm going to be here forever means that I don't have to cram everything into the next 60 years.

204
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
 That if I want to go to Thailand, I don't have to go to Thailand in the next 60 years.

205
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:48,000
 I can go to Thailand in 600 years.

206
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:57,000
 And I can see Thailand in its redeemed state, in its perfect state, without sin, disease, and death.

207
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 I can go to Thailand. I'll go one day. You can go with me.

208
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:09,000
 And we'll see it without sex trafficking, without the corruption that sin has ushered in there.

209
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 And if you think the beaches there are beautiful now, you should see them.

210
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 We will see them in their redeemed state.

211
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,000
 And I don't need to experience that now.

212
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:23,000
 I've got the rest of the rest of the rest to experience that.

213
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:26,000
 Because that's the world I belong to.

214
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:29,000
 It's a new world here.

215
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 Right now I live in this broken world like you as a foreigner and in exile.

216
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 And so until then, friend, hang on.

217
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,000
 Stay the course.

218
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:49,000
 If this life feels really hard, it's beating you down, relax.

219
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,000
 It's not the world you belong to.

220
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:55,000
 It's not the one you will exist in forever.

221
00:13:55,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 Give yourself fully to the work of the Lord and create time and space to renew your mind around that reality.

222
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:05,000
 Every day, it's important, every day there's two kinds of people here.

223
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 There's those of you that have been with Jesus today.

224
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:15,000
 There's those of you who say you know him but you spent zero time with him today.

225
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,000
 And you don't know him.

226
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:20,000
 If you didn't spend time with him, you don't know him.

227
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:26,000
 If you have not prioritized him today, you don't know him as you should.

228
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,000
 I pray that you get to know him.

229
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 When I go to Africa, I'm a visitor on a mission.

230
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,000
 My days there are purposeful.

231
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,000
 I don't just kind of make that place like I'm staying at home.

