00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,000
 Here's what was really going on.

495
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,000
 They're all hypocrites.

496
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 They love when you fail.

497
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 They're watching you.

498
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 A guy asked me the other day, he said,

499
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:19,000
 "Hey, man, what's the best way to share the gospel with your family?"

500
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 Because we agree, man, family's hard.

501
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 Like family, that's a tough one.

502
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,000
 He says, "Man, they know me.

503
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 They have seen me at my worst.

504
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:33,000
 And so, man, how do I share the gospel with them?"

505
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 And I just said, "Let me ask you a question.

506
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:38,000
 Have they seen you change?"

507
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 Because that's the foundation of sharing the gospel with them.

508
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 Displaying the change that Christ has brought in your life.

509
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 "Yeah, man, but listen, I'm not perfect."

510
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 Exactly.

511
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,000
 You're not perfect.

512
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 You need a Savior.

513
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:52,000
 You need a process for when they see you not perfect,

514
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:54,000
 that you go back to your mom and your dad,

515
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 and you look them in the eyes, and you say, "Hey, will you forgive me?

516
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 That's not who I am.

517
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,000
 That's who I was.

518
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 You guys remember, that's who I was.

519
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 That's not who I am, though.

520
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 Will you please forgive me for what I just did, for what I just said,

521
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:08,000
 for how I just reacted, for how I just treated my siblings,

522
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 for how I treated you?

523
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 Will you please forgive me?"

524
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:14,000
 And that process, that will minister to them.

525
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:19,000
 You humbling yourself, showing them that you are led by another spirit,

526
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 not the spirit of this world.

527
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 And so who has God placed in your life so that you might be an example to them?

528
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 Who has God placed you in their life so that they might come to know him

529
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:40,000
 and glorify him on the day he visits?

530
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 Which could mean their conversion.

531
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:45,000
 It could mean when Christ comes back.

532
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 It could be this time right now between the first and second coming.

533
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 Theologians disagree on what that means right there.

534
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 But as I thought about it and thought about how to teach it to you,

535
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,000
 it doesn't change our application.

536
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 God is going to be glorified by your friends coming to know him in a greater way

537
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 by the things that you do around them.

538
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,000
 That's what matters.

539
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
 You're an example.

540
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:11,000
 You may be the only Bible they ever read.

541
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,000
 You may be the only verse they ever memorize.

542
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 Watching your life.

543
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
 There was a guy who discipled me.

544
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
 He's an unbelievably godly man, knows the word,

545
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 sat down with me when I became a Christian.

546
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,000
 And we just started in Genesis 1-1.

547
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,000
 And we just started going verse by verse through the Bible.

548
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 And he started teaching me.

549
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 He's one of these guys.

550
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,000
 I mean, he loves his wife.

551
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 He disciples his children.

552
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:41,000
 He's really cool, calm, and collective all the time.

553
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:44,000
 He's just a spirit-led guy.

554
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 And I can't even imagine him as a pagan, but I've heard stories.

555
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:51,000
 I've heard stories about how he just used to get wasted, how he used to party,

556
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 the way he used to treat girls.

557
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:58,000
 But I can't even get my head around that because I only know the saved version of him.

558
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:02,000
 And the way that it happened is he would go to these fraternity parties in college.

559
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:07,000
 And he would just get, you know, plastered.

560
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 But he always saw these same two guys who never drank.

561
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,000
 They were kind to everybody.

562
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 Everybody liked them.

563
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 When people would make fun of them, they didn't seem to affect them at all.

564
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 They just kind of shrug it off, go about their day, and they were always having fun.

565
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:26,000
 And he said he would see those same two guys all the time.

566
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:30,000
 And one day he asked them, "Man, how do you do this?"

567
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:33,000
 And he got to know those guys, and he got to know their Jesus.

568
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 And he became a Christian.

569
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,000
 When I get to have--I don't know these guys.

570
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 I know the two of them.

571
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:43,000
 But when I get to heaven, I'm going to find them, and I'm going to thank them

572
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:47,000
 because they had a profound impact on my life even though we've never met.

573
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:53,000
 Their example God used to save a man who poured his life into mine

574
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,000
 so that I might teach you tonight.

575
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:58,000
 How great is God?

576
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 And so people trust Christians before they trust Christ.

577
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 People most often will trust a Christian before they will trust Jesus.

578
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 Jesus said it.

579
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,000
 Peter's just saying Jesus' words.

580
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:10,000
 In Matthew 5:16, Jesus said it like this.

581
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:15,000
 "In the same way, let your light shine before others that they may see your good deeds

582
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,000
 and glorify your Father in heaven."

583
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:28,000
 So there is something about the way that we act that is groundwork for the gospel.

584
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:31,000
 As I think about all of these passages, and I think about my own life

585
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:34,000
 and I just look back on the sins that I've given myself to--

586
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:38,000
 if you don't know, if we don't know each other, I mean, I was an alcoholic, drug user,

587
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:46,000
 porn addict, sex addict, just abuser of women in the way that I treated them.

588
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:51,000
 And God came in, and he gave me something so much better.

589
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:54,000
 But as I think about the times when my guard is down,

590
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 it's almost always when I forget that I'm not home.

591
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,000
 It starts there.

592
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,000
 I start trying to make this place my home.

593
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 I start pursuing my comforts.

594
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 I stop doing the things that I should do.

595
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:08,000
 I stop prioritizing time with Jesus that particular morning.

596
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:11,000
 I get in the afternoon, and I just want to be comfortable,

597
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:15,000
 and I'm tempted to give into my flesh,

598
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:21,000
 to invite the desires that wage war against my soul into my soul,

599
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 to lower my guard, and to invite guilt and shame to rule.

600
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 Christ has something better than that.

601
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,000
 And so if you're here, you might be asking,

602
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:38,000
 "Well, what if it costs me when I don't go to happy hour?

603
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,000
 Like I don't have that team camaraderie,

604
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:43,000
 and they begin to talk about me like I'm weird,

605
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:46,000
 and what if I remain single forever because I'm unwilling to date like he does

606
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:49,000
 or dress like she does?

607
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:53,000
 And what if I don't get the promotion because I won't go to the strip clubs?

608
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:59,000
 And what if my family thinks that I spend too much time at church?

609
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:03,000
 What if I suffer for doing good?"

610
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:07,000
 Here's how this chapter ends.

611
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:11,000
 "If you suffer for doing good and you endure it,

612
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,000
 this is commendable before God.

613
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:17,000
 To this you were called because Christ suffered for you,

614
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:24,000
 leaving you," underline this, "as leaving you an example that you should follow in his steps.

615
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:28,000
 He committed no sin and no deceit was found in his mouth.

616
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:31,000
 When they hurled insults at him, he did not retaliate.

617
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:34,000
 When he suffered, he made no threats.

618
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:38,000
 Instead, he entrusted himself to him who judges justly.

619
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,000
 He himself bore our sins.

620
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:43,000
 He paid for our sins in his body on the cross

621
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:47,000
 so that we might die to sins and live for righteousness.

622
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:50,000
 By his wounds you have been healed."

623
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:54,000
 And so we're examples to others.

624
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:57,000
 But we have an example in Jesus to follow.

625
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:00,000
 And if you feel right now, listen, this is so important,

626
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:03,000
 if you feel like right now, you're like, "Man, I can't. I'm just like a dog to his vomit.

627
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:06,000
 I keep going back to the same sins, the same websites.

628
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:10,000
 When I'm by myself, that desire is too big for me to fight.

629
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,000
 I'm tired of fighting it.

630
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,000
 I don't know how to win.

631
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,000
 And I don't want to end this relationship.

632
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:19,000
 I mean, you might call it an idol, but I call it love.

633
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:24,000
 And we're going to see where this goes."

634
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:27,000
 You know your struggle.

635
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:30,000
 And you're like, "I can't win." You can't win.

636
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,000
 Jesus won for you.

637
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:35,000
 Jesus paid for it.

638
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:38,000
 You have an example to follow.

639
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:41,000
 You cannot win without following Christ.

640
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:44,000
 You're a Christ follower, a Christian.

641
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:48,000
 You have to keep your eyes on the author and the perfecter of our faith.

642
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:55,000
 Jesus Christ, who for the joy set before Him, endured the cross,

643
00:40:55,000 --> 00:41:00,000
 scorning its shame for you and for me.

644
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:04,000
 He's the only one that's been here, that came from there,

645
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:06,000
 to hear and endure this place,

646
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 who didn't do all the things that we shouldn't do,

647
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:17,000
 and who lived the righteous life that we desire on our behalf.

648
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,000
 I told you I love to travel.

649
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:25,000
 And my favorite place is a place in Mexico,

650
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,000
 kind of the Riviera Maya, Playa del Carmen area.

651
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:31,000
 It's where I went for the first time on my honeymoon with Monica.

652
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:34,000
 And so for the past 12 years, we've gone back every year.

653
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:37,000
 And I kind of pride myself as being an expert on that area.

654
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,000
 I mean, if I lost my job in ministry,

655
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:41,000
 I think I'd go be a travel agent of sorts

656
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:44,000
 and just help people plan their honeymoons in the Riviera Maya,

657
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:46,000
 because I love it.

658
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:50,000
 And my friend Elena, who's on staff here, is getting married this weekend,

659
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:54,000
 and she's honeymooning in the Riviera Maya.

660
00:41:54,000 --> 00:42:00,000
 And she didn't ask me my opinion, which was extremely offensive.

661
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:03,000
 And so I'm like, "Elena!" She's like, "I can't talk about it.

662
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,000
 It's just too stressful. All the details are done."

663
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:09,000
 So I go, and I book an appointment on her calendar.

664
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:12,000
 I'm like, "We're going to talk about this."

665
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:15,000
 And we sit down, and I'm like,

666
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,000
 "What do you want to do on your honeymoon besides that?

667
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,000
 What do you want to do on your honeymoon?"

668
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,000
 And I'm like, "Where do you want to go?

669
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,000
 Do you want adventure? Do you want relaxation?

670
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:26,000
 What do you want it to look like?"

671
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:29,000
 And she starts to tell me, "Well, we like to go and do a little bit,

672
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,000
 but we want to relax a lot by the pool, by the beach."

